6: You're finally here. Now help me.
10:
Uh, we don't mind lending a hand,
but... What exactly do you need help
with?
14: No time to explain. Follow me.
19:
What, she can't be bothered to
explain? She's the one that asked us
to come...
23:
Maybe it's an emergency? We
should at least check things out.
28:
I'm Ram. I'll be watching over you
today. But for the most part, you
should look after yourselves.
30:
If you need anything, ask the two
behind me. Understood?
35:
Whoooa, hold on... Are you telling us
to babysit these kids?
41:
You're not as slow as you look. Yes,
that's what I'm saying. I didn't want
to do this job alone.
46:
Is this a request from the Guild? If it
wasn't something you wanted to do,
why'd you accept it?
50:
I didn't. Barusu got carried away and
randomly accepted it.
54: This extra work is his fault.
63:
Sounds to me like this is YOUR mess
to clean up, not ours—
68: Big fluffy kitty! You can talk? So cool!
71:
Yes, he's a big fluffy kitty that can
talk. Pet him as much as you like.
77: Ram, read this book for me.
80:
Don't you remember what I said? If
you need anything, ask those two—
82: But I don't wanna. I want you.
85:
You can wait for your mother and
father to come home and read it to
you instead.
87: But I don't have a mom anymore.
89:
She got attacked by monsters in the
village we lived in before.
92:
All right, I understand. For you, I'll
read the book.
95:
Come sit. Once we're done reading,
I'll give you some helpful life tips.
111:
Are those... potatoes? That's a lot of
them.
116:
I made steamed potatoes—and I
had some help, as you can see.
Don't tell me you're a picky eater.
121:
N-no, of course not! Steamed
potatoes are great, high in
nutrition... They seem to be the "in"
food recently...
130: Ram, what's wrong? Are you okay?
132:
I'm just a little tired, that's all. Don't
worry about me.
136:
Let's dig in. They're cooked—no,
steamed to perfection.
142:
Urk, I'm gonna be sick... Stomach's so
full... Can't move...
147:
I guess with those two out of
commission, it's my turn to look after
you all.
150:
Everyone, gather around. I'll read
books to you and teach you useful
life lessons.
153:
Pay attention, and you'll be able to
help your father out someday.
155:
If you have any questions, look up
the answers on your own later.
158:
I'm going to read you a book about
the Farlan faith. Have any of you
heard about the Star Angel?
162:
That's something the Palpebran
church believes in, right? I'm
surprised you know so much...
165:
I learned of it when I was gathering
information. You never know when
something might come in handy.
168:
I know about the angel! They're
someone amazing, right?
171:
That's a vague way to put it. It
seems you'll need to learn about the
founding of Palpebra and the
Farlands as well.
174:
History can teach you surprising
lessons, you know.
184:
That's because I am. She probably
knows more about all this than I do.
It's honestly impressive...
191:
Those kids loved you, Ram! Aren't
you glad you went through with the
job?
194:
I'm more concerned about finding a
way back to our real home.
198:
I'll have even less time for that if I'm
asked to babysit again.
201: What? I'm not wrong, am I?
205: Nah, you're not. Don't mind me.
209:
Anyway, I'm off. I appreciate your
help today.
212:
I look forward to your assistance if
they ask us to babysit again.
215:
As repayment, I'll help you on your
adventures when you need a hand.
220: Sounds good to me! Thanks, Ram.
224:
It's only fair. See you later, Alk.
Nimbus.
